theorem Topology.closure_union_interior_eq_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    closure ((A : Set X) ∪ interior A) = closure A := by
  -- First inclusion: `closure (A ∪ interior A) ⊆ closure A`.
  have h₁ : closure ((A : Set X) ∪ interior A) ⊆ closure A := by
    -- Since `A ⊆ closure A` and `interior A ⊆ A ⊆ closure A`,
    -- the union is contained in `closure A`.
    have h_subset : ((A : Set X) ∪ interior A) ⊆ closure A := by
      intro x hx
      cases hx with
      | inl hA =>
          exact subset_closure hA
      | inr hInt =>
          have : (x : X) ∈ (A : Set X) := interior_subset hInt
          exact subset_closure this
    exact closure_mono h_subset
  -- Second inclusion: `closure A ⊆ closure (A ∪ interior A)`.
  have h₂ : closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure ((A : Set X) ∪ interior A) := by
    -- Trivial set‐inclusion `A ⊆ A ∪ interior A`.
    have h_subset : (A : Set X) ⊆ (A : Set X) ∪ interior A := by
      intro x hx
      exact Or.inl hx
    exact closure_mono h_subset
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h₂
